Minimize frequent design changes during the build phase to ensure stability and reduce rework, enabling smoother progress and timely completion of the project.
Emphasize the importance of clearly defining requirements before the build phase begins to prevent misunderstandings, enhance efficiency, and align stakeholders' expectations.
Improve the impact analysis process by thoroughly evaluating business reports to avoid confusion during User Acceptance Testing (UAT) and ensure the system meets the desired objectives.
Address timeline shrinkage for testing and UAT by allocating adequate resources, setting realistic schedules, and managing priorities effectively to maintain quality while meeting project deadlines.
Implement a development practice that includes thorough unit testing before handing over the code to the Quality Assurance (QA) team, ensuring higher code quality, reducing bugs, and expediting the testing process.
